description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The East of England Ambulance Service is looking to appoint a Head of Education &amp; Training Delivery. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Postholder is responsible for ensuring that education, training delivery, practice and leadership is embedded within the Trust, supporting the development and implementation of the national and local paramedic standards of proficiency, delivering quality clinical practice.&lt;br /&gt;The role has four key strands: expert practitioner, leadership and consultancy, training and development and research and evaluation. Overall, it will offer strategic clinical leadership and be the pinnacle of the career pathway for our paramedics&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The ideal candidate will have:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Batchelors degree or equivalent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Masters level teaching qualification&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evidence of audit and evaluation / benchmarking of clinical services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate knowledge of all pillars of academic activity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;They will be a recognised training expert, rooted in paramedic practice and able to assist in setting education and training standards and implement them across the Trust and ensure quality education and training across the organisation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is a key senior role in the Education and Training Team and will work as part of a team delivering high quality and education to our learners and to existing staff, supporting them in their continued professional development.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jessica Watts,Head of Improvement Programmes&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jessica.Watts@eastamb.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
